# US-02 · UX · Sprint 1

## Real-time typing feedback

**As a player**, I want immediate visual feedback when I type characters correctly or incorrectly, so that I can quickly recognize mistakes and improve my typing accuracy during gameplay.

---

## Acceptance criteria

* [ ] Correctly typed characters are highlighted in green
* [ ] Incorrect characters are highlighted in red
* [ ] Incorrect input does not advance progress on the snippet
* [ ] Feedback updates instantly as the player types

---

## Notes

Typing games depend heavily on responsiveness. If feedback feels delayed or unclear, the gameplay quickly becomes frustrating. Correct and incorrect states should be visually obvious at a glance without distracting from the horror atmosphere. The player should feel constantly connected to the typing mechanic.

## Dependencies

* Core typing input system must exist
* UI text rendering system must support dynamic styling
* Snippet progression system must track character accuracy

## Definition of done

While typing a snippet, players receive immediate visual feedback for every character entered. Correct characters display differently from incorrect ones, and invalid input does not incorrectly progress the snippet.
